commit.message:
Replace use of Optional in type annotations

Since we use `from __future__ import annotations` type annotations
will be ignored as strings. We can use `type | None` even on older
Python versions.

commit.message:
Declare Python 3.10 support. Update CI, version, changelog (#28)

* Declare Python 3.10 support. Update CI, version, changelog

Versions in YAML quoted to force parsing as strings. Otherwise 3.10 is parsed as 3.1.

Further reading
- https://dev.to/hugovk/the-python-3-1-problem-85g
- https://yaml-online-parser.appspot.com/?yaml=mangled+version%3A+3.10%0Aright+version%3A+%223.10%22&type=json

* CI: Upgrade to actions/setup-python@v2 to install newer Pythons

From https://github.com/actions/setup-python#readme

> Ability to download, install and set up Python packages from
actions/python-versions that do not come preinstalled on runners.

* CI: Suppress flake8 check that exceptions should be called "...Error"

fixes #30
